<section xml:id="surfaces_in_space">
  <title>Surfaces in Space</title>
<objectives>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <p>
        To identify the equations and important geometric information of quadric surfaces
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        To identify and plot other common surfaces such as <m>z=f(x,y)</m> and cylinder surfaces
      </p>
    </li>
  </ul>
</objectives>
<subsection>
  <title>Quadric and Cylinder Surfaces</title>
  <question>
    <p>
      Using your newly found understanding of surfaces, draw a good plot of each equation by hand. Be sure to label your graphs.
      <ol>
        <li><m>25x^2+4y^2+100z^2=100</m></li>
        <li><m>25x^2+4y^2-100z^2=100</m></li>
        <li><m>-25x^2-4y^2+100z^2=100</m></li>
        <li><m>25x^2-4y^2=0</m></li>
        <li><m>25x^2+4y^2+100z^2=0</m></li>
        <li><m>25x^2+4y^2+100z=0</m></li>
        <li><m>25x^2-4y^2+100z=0</m></li>
        <li><m>-4y^2+100z=0</m></li>
        <li><m>25x+4y+100z=100</m></li>
        <li><m>-25x^2-4y^2-100z^2=100</m></li>
        <li><m>25x^2-4y^2+100z^2=-100</m></li>
      </ol>
    </p>
  </question>

</subsection>

</section>

